modules.description: Generates and renders 2D vector graphics with support for lines, shapes, and text. It handles canvas dimensions, color specifications, and coordinate transformations. Users can create interactive plots directly within Jupyter notebooks and export them as static images.

provides a framework for integrating OCaml with Jupyter notebooks through a set of modular components includes basic types for kernel communication and message handling, with no additional operations defined allows for extension by other modules that implement specific notebook interactions supports foundational setup for interactive OCaml sessions within a Jupyter environment
